these are reasonable things

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:18.950
to say, given the assumption
that this first statement is

00:00:18.950 --> 00:00:21.610
true, that eating spinach
makes you stronger.

00:00:21.610 --> 00:00:23.270
And we could even
put it over here.

00:00:23.270 --> 00:00:29.830
"Eating spinach
makes you stronger."

00:00:29.830 --> 00:00:31.530
So let's read this
first sentence.

00:00:31.530 --> 00:00:35.152
"If you eat spinach, then
you will get stronger."

00:00:35.152 --> 00:00:37.360
So this is just really a
rephrasing of the first one.

00:00:37.360 --> 00:00:39.590
This is really just
putting it in if-then form.

00:00:39.590 --> 00:00:43.110
You have your "if" and
your "then," but it's

00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:44.640
really saying the same thing.

00:00:44.640 --> 00:00:47.810
If you eat spinach-- that's
the same thing as eating

00:00:47.810 --> 00:00:52.220
the spinach-- then you
will become stronger,

00:00:52.220 --> 00:00:55.630
then you will be stronger.

00:00:55.630 --> 00:00:56.720
You get stronger.

00:00:56.720 --> 00:00:58.650
So this is saying
the exact same thing.

00:00:58.650 --> 00:01:02.200
I will say that if we assume
this first statement is true,

00:01:02.200 --> 00:01:05.230
then the second statement
is definitely true.

00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:06.420
Now, this third statement.

00:01:06.420 --> 00:01:11.800
"If you don't eat spinach, then
